Find the best authors.

best_authors <- books %>% 
  select(authors, average_rating) %>% 
  group_by(authors) %>% 
  summarise(best = median(average_rating)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(best)) %>% 
  head(n = 100)

Calculate which publisher has the most books.

most_books <- books %>% 
  select(publisher, bookID) %>% 
  group_by(publisher) %>% 
  mutate(total = bookID - bookID + 1) %>% 
  count(total) %>% 
  arrange(desc(n))
